# Ignore-rect mask for regression_smoke (NumOS SDL2 emulator visual test).
#
# Reason: the ONLY volatile region on this RegressionApp screen across separate
# launches is the StatusBar clock. The app opens on its "Data" tab showing a static
# 2-column X/Y table with one empty row; RegressionApp has no update() method, no
# blinking input cursor (the cell editor is not open at screenshot time), and no
# animation once its 200 ms fade-in settles, so the body (tab bar, X/Y headers, the
# empty table grid, the footer hint) is byte-stable. The clock label is drawn by
# StatusBar::updateClock() from the real wall clock (time() -> localtime ->
# "%02d:%02d", src/ui/StatusBar.cpp), so HH:MM reflects the minute each scripted run
# happens to execute on. Two launches in different minutes (or hours) therefore
# differ only inside the clock glyphs. This is expected per-minute UI
# nondeterminism, NOT a renderer bug — the renderer is frozen, so it is masked in
# the comparator instead of edited in src/.
#
# Region: the SAME shared StatusBar clock rect as statistics_smoke / probability_smoke /
# sequences_smoke / settings_smoke / math_showcase_smoke. The label is aligned
# LV_ALIGN_LEFT_MID,6 in lv_font_montserrat_12 (StatusBar.cpp:61-65) and is always
# exactly 5 glyphs ("HH:MM"), so its box spans ~x[6..38] y[8..16]. Because both the
# HOUR and the MINUTE digits can vary across arbitrary launches, the mask covers the
# WHOLE label, not just the minutes.
#
# Rect = full HH:MM label box (~x[6..38] y[8..16]) padded ~2px on each side ->
# x[4..40] y[6..18]. This is tight to the clock: the app title "Regression" is
# centered (x~160), the angle/battery indicators are right-aligned (x>240), and the
# Regression body (Data/Equation/Graph tab bar + the X/Y table) renders below the
# y=24 StatusBar separator — none are masked. In particular the Data table content
# is NOT covered.
#
# x,y,w,h
4,6,37,13
